header.gameNote: NEW YORK LIFE ACC MEN'S TOURNAMENT - FINAL

videos.description: ACC defensive player of the year Isaiah Wilkins strips the ball loose and takes it all the way for a wide-open dunk.
videos.headline: Wilkins' active hands sets up sweet slap

videos.description: Devon Hall fades to the corner for an 3-pointer off a feed from Kyle Guy.
videos.headline: Hall hits nothing but net from 3

videos.description: Theo Pinson grabs the rebound, runs the break and delivers pass to Luke Maye for a layup.
videos.headline: Maye goes up-and-under to tie it for UNC

videos.description: Seventh Woods gets beats off the dribble, but recovers and blocks the shot into the first row.
videos.headline: Woods sends a shot into the stands

videos.description: Theo Pinson drives to the paint and just puts enough on it for his first basket of the game.
videos.headline: Ball hangs on the rim for Pinson's first bucket

videos.description: Virginia runs the same place twice and both resulted in a wide-open, two-handed dunks for Jack Salt and Isaiah Wilkins.
videos.headline: Virginia runs the same play, gets same result

videos.description: Cameron Johnson takes a hard foul and has to be helped to his feet before leaving the game.
videos.headline: Johnson shaken up after hard fall

videos.description: De'Andre Hunter just gets the ball up over Luke Maye and knocks down a short jumper before the shot clock buzzer sounds.
videos.headline: Hunter sinks jumper before buzzer

videos.description: Kyle Guy says it took everything for Virginia to come out on top against North Carolina in the ACC final.
videos.headline: Guy: 'We're 66.7% of the way done'

videos.description: Fifth-year player Devon Hall credits North Carolina for being a "heck of a team" in the ACC championship game.
videos.headline: Hall: ACC win is 'special'

videos.description: Tony Bennett says his team's ability to play so well together is what makes them special.
videos.headline: Bennett: Virginia has 'uncommon chemistry'
